actually said.

For example, it says this is a bill of NON-rights, because everyone except
the writer's ilk are too dim to understand. He's smarter than the dim ones,
it appears, so he's out to tell people what they CAN'T demand. For example,
they can't demand that other people stop being offensive. They damned well
can demand that, although they aren't likely to get anywhere with it.

