&gt; No, Ed, the upside-down view of rights is the idea that people *are*
&gt; entitled
&gt; to have the nice things of life without working for them, the idea that
&gt; people
&gt; *are* entitled to go through life without ever being offended by hearing
&gt; views
&gt; they disagree with, and so on. *That* is what's upside down.
